"jsonContent":{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s14",
"title":{
"__html":"Chronic Diarrhea"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"9b2e78",
"children":[
"Chronic Diarrhea"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s14_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"86a64c",
"children":[
"Chronic diarrhea is defined as lasting at least 4 weeks. Except for ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Giardia lamblia"
]
},
", infectious causes of chronic diarrhea are uncommon in immunocompetent adults."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"31a72d",
"children":[
"Osmotic diarrhea is most commonly caused by lactase deficiency. It is associated with eating, improves with fasting, and is not nocturnal."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"704a1c",
"children":[
"Secretory diarrhea is characterized by large-volume, watery, nocturnal bowel movements and is unchanged by fasting (see also Celiac Disease)."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s14_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2efa30",
"children":[
"Select colonoscopy for most patients with chronic diarrhea; biopsies of the colonic mucosa should be performed to assess for microscopic colitis."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"82d0e0",
"children":[
"Additional testing is based on pretest probability of disease."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"109c56",
"children":[
"Blood or an elevated fecal calprotectin level supports ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"inflammatory bowel disease",
"children":[
"IBD"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"396103",
"children":[
"Stool or urine laxative screen supports laxative abuse."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"01362d",
"children":[
"A reduced fecal elastase level supports chronic pancreatitis."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f673ca",
"children":[
"A positive 72-hour stool collection for fecal fat confirms steatorrhea."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"622881",
"children":[
"The four most common disorders causing steatorrhea are:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"957c0a",
"children":[
"celiac disease"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"cd424a",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"small intestinal bacterial overgrowth",
"children":[
"SIBO"
]
},
" "
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b2d29b",
"children":[
"short-bowel syndrome"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"59bf38",
"children":[
"pancreatic insufficiency"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"051e2c",
"children":[
"Stool electrolytes (sodium and potassium) can be measured in liquid stool to calculate the fecal osmotic gap, which helps to diagnose osmotic diarrhea. The osmotic gap is calculated as 290 − (2 × [Na + K])."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e2a808",
"children":[
"An osmotic gap >100 mOsm/kg H",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"O indicates osmotic diarrhea."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0958e5",
"children":[
"A gap <50 mOsm/kg H",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sub",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"2"
]
},
"O indicates secretory diarrhea."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_gi_s14_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5575dc",
"children":[
"Don't forget other causes of diarrhea such as sorbitol (added as a sweetener to gum, candy) and medications, including ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
"s,"
]
},
" magnesium-containing antacids, metformin, colchicine, and antibiotics."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"acb40b",
"children":[
"Infection with ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"G. lamblia"
]
},
" should be considered in patients with exposure to young children or potentially contaminated water (lakes and streams)."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s14_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"26e019",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 55-year-old woman who takes ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs",
"children":[
"NSAIDs"
]
},
" daily has watery diarrhea without weight loss. Colonoscopy is grossly normal."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4ebbd0",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, select microscopic colitis; biopsy confirms the diagnosis."
]
}
]
}
]
},
